00:53:43,410 --> 00:53:47,708
Could you hand me my gown, please?
It's in the suitcase.

441
00:53:53,918 --> 00:53:56,009
The pink one with the white edging.

442
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:08,691
Ow! Thank you.

443
00:54:11,663 --> 00:54:13,823
Sorry.

444
00:54:24,472 --> 00:54:26,735
Sorry.

445
00:54:35,079 --> 00:54:37,171
Sorry.

446
00:54:58,662 --> 00:55:01,152
Thank you very much. Thank you.

447
00:55:33,353 --> 00:55:37,880
<i>That morning, Xi saw the ugliest
person he'd ever come across.</i>

448
00:55:38,257 --> 00:55:41,885
<i>She was as pale as something
that had crawled out of a rotting log.</i>

449
00:55:42,060 --> 00:55:43,720
<i>Her hair was quite gruesome...</i>

450
00:55:43,894 --> 00:55:46,987
<i>...long and stringy and white,
as if she was very old.</i>

451
00:55:47,130 --> 00:55:48,527
<i>She was very big.</i>

452
00:55:48,697 --> 00:55:52,996
<i>You'd have to dig the whole day
to find enough food to feed her.</i>

453
00:55:59,237 --> 00:56:01,034
Go away.

454
00:56:04,242 --> 00:56:07,074
<i>Although it was a hot day,
she was wearing skins...</i>

455
00:56:07,244 --> 00:56:10,905
<i>...that looked as if they
were made from cobwebs.</i>

456
00:56:15,048 --> 00:56:17,573
<i>She was doing strange
and magical things.</i>

457
00:56:17,751 --> 00:56:20,116
<i>It struck him that she must be
one of the gods.</i>

458
00:56:20,286 --> 00:56:22,618
<i>He wondered what she
was doing on earth.</i>

459
00:56:22,788 --> 00:56:25,778
<i>He was glad he met her.
He'd give her the evil thing...</i>

460
00:56:25,957 --> 00:56:27,924
<i>...and go home to his family.</i>

461
00:56:28,092 --> 00:56:32,424
<i>He said tactfully that he didn't need
the thing, and she could have it back.</i>

462
00:56:32,594 --> 00:56:36,325
<i>But she was very rude,
and she walked away.</i>

463
00:56:40,534 --> 00:56:43,933
- That's a Bushman. How'd he get here?
- I don't know. He's rude.

464
00:56:44,269 --> 00:56:46,828
<i>There was another god.
He had a fire inside him.</i>

465
00:56:47,038 --> 00:56:49,768
<i>The smoke came out
through his mouth and nostrils.</i>

466
00:56:50,107 --> 00:56:53,473
<i>Xi said politely, "It was kind of you
to send us this thing...</i>

467
00:56:53,676 --> 00:56:56,473
<i>...but it made my family unhappy.
Please take it. "</i>

468
00:56:56,644 --> 00:56:58,805
<i>Sorry, no sabe.</i>

469
00:56:59,613 --> 00:57:01,080
Where's the truck?

470
00:57:15,358 --> 00:57:18,087
I'll try and get it down.

471
00:57:18,260 --> 00:57:22,787
<i>There was a peculiar sound, and Xi saw
a most amazing animal approaching.</i>

472
00:57:22,996 --> 00:57:25,463
<i>Its legs went around
instead of up and down.</i>

473
00:57:25,631 --> 00:57:28,156
<i>And there was
a weird-looking god on its back.</i>

474
00:57:28,334 --> 00:57:31,063
<i>He wore blue skin on his head
and red on his body.</i>

475
00:57:31,201 --> 00:57:33,102
<i>And hair grew on his face.</i>

476
00:57:33,270 --> 00:57:37,138
What the hell happened?
Where have you been?

477
00:57:37,306 --> 00:57:39,774
<i>The funny thing was
that they couldn't speak.</i>

478
00:57:39,941 --> 00:57:41,670
<i>They made sounds like monkeys.</i>

479
00:57:41,977 --> 00:57:46,071
- Hi.
- What happened? Where's the antichrist?

480
00:57:48,982 --> 00:57:52,576
What the hell did you do that for, huh?

481
00:57:52,783 --> 00:57:55,274
I'll tell you later. Let's get it down.

482
00:57:55,452 --> 00:57:58,512
And the little Bushman?
What's he doing in these parts?

483
00:57:58,721 --> 00:58:01,815
I don't know. He was trying
to tell me something.

484
00:58:03,491 --> 00:58:06,152
- You speak Bushman?
- Yeah.

485
00:58:09,629 --> 00:58:12,222
<i>The hairy one could speak.</i>

486
00:58:17,401 --> 00:58:20,392
He says, "Thanks for the bottle,
but you can have it back."

487
00:58:20,603 --> 00:58:22,092
I didn't give it to him.

488
00:58:22,538 --> 00:58:26,473
- Well, he don't want the bottle.
- Then he'd better throw it away.

489
00:58:27,542 --> 00:58:32,136
<i>The hairy one said, "We don't want it.
You'll have to throw it away yourself. "</i>

490
00:58:32,478 --> 00:58:34,241
<i>Xi was very disappointed.</i>

491
00:58:34,413 --> 00:58:37,813
<i>It was unfair of the gods to make him
throw it off the earth.</i>

492
00:58:37,982 --> 00:58:42,884
<i>In fact, he began to doubt
whether they really were gods.</i>

493
00:58:53,927 --> 00:58:56,895
Get out! Get out!
Get out! Get in there.

494
00:58:57,062 --> 00:59:00,224
Get in there! Move it! Move it!

495
00:59:00,398 --> 00:59:04,231
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

496
00:59:30,852 --> 00:59:34,446
Yes, yes, yes. Here comes
the great white hunter to the rescue.

497
00:59:34,689 --> 00:59:36,178
Miss Thompson, I presume.

498
00:59:36,357 --> 00:59:39,847
Hello, Steyn. How would you like
to travel in style for a change?

499
00:59:40,025 --> 00:59:42,516
Yes, thank you.

500
00:59:43,661 --> 00:59:47,096
How do you open this thing?
With a can opener?

501
00:59:51,167 --> 00:59:53,600
Quaint. Milady?

502
00:59:53,768 --> 00:59:57,258
- Thank you very much, Mr. Steyn, for...
- Bye-bye, Steyn.

503
00:59:57,438 --> 00:59:58,699
Goodbye, Miss Thompson.

504
00:59:58,871 --> 01:00:00,463
By the way, I am Jack Hind.

505
01:00:00,673 --> 01:00:03,698
The Reverend's worried.
He got to me on the short-wave...

506
01:00:03,875 --> 01:00:07,037
...so I offered to look for you.
That was very sweet of me.

507
01:00:07,211 --> 01:00:09,735
- It sure was.
- Would you like to sit over there?

508
01:00:09,913 --> 01:00:11,107
Sure.

509
01:00:11,281 --> 01:00:14,078
Thank you, Mr. Steyn.

510
01:00:15,049 --> 01:00:17,483
See you, Steyn. See you, Mpudi.

511
01:00:52,143 --> 01:00:54,610
I don't want to talk about it.

512
01:00:56,145 --> 01:00:59,137
She thinks I'm a lunatic,
and I don't blame her.

513
01:00:59,314 --> 01:01:04,478
You know, she asks me what do I do,
and I say I collect manure.

514
01:01:04,652 --> 01:01:07,915
I don't tell her I analyse it
for my doctoral thesis.

515
01:01:08,086 --> 01:01:11,418
I bet you she thinks I shovel the stuff.

516
01:01:14,024 --> 01:01:15,287
Was it rough?

517
01:01:15,459 --> 01:01:18,120
I'd rather not talk about it.

518
01:01:18,295 --> 01:01:19,727
That rough.

519
01:01:19,862 --> 01:01:23,024
It won't be long now,
and your suffering will be over.

520
01:01:23,298 --> 01:01:26,960
When you get there, you'll have to
stand there and look beautiful...

521
01:01:27,134 --> 01:01:30,261
...while the whole tribe sings
their welcome song at you.

522
01:01:30,469 --> 01:01:33,460
Then you can relax, have a bath
and a nice breakfast.

523
01:01:34,039 --> 01:01:37,667
Is it true that when a rhino sees a fire,
he stamps it out?

524
01:01:37,875 --> 01:01:41,934
Where did you hear that one?
Did Steyn tell you?

525
01:01:42,144 --> 01:01:43,940
Why would he tell you that?

526
01:01:44,279 --> 01:01:46,769
I'd rather not talk about it.

527
01:01:46,946 --> 01:01:50,939
- Here. This'll put hair on your chest.
- That's all I need.

528
01:01:54,752 --> 01:01:58,279
She wouldn't believe me about
the warthog and the rhinoceros.

529
01:01:58,455 --> 01:02:01,288
- What bloody rhinoceros?
- I don't want to talk about it.

530
01:02:01,458 --> 01:02:04,323
So how did this thing get up the tree?

531
01:02:04,492 --> 01:02:08,359
She got stuck in a watape tree
and I had to...

532
01:02:08,529 --> 01:02:12,055
You know she's got flowers
on her panties?

533
01:02:13,032 --> 01:02:15,397
So that's how this thing got up the tree.

534
01:02:15,635 --> 01:02:17,692
Yes.

535
01:02:57,664 --> 01:02:59,858
Don't I wave or take a bow
or something?

536
01:03:00,032 --> 01:03:01,692
No.

537
01:03:19,579 --> 01:03:22,911
<i>Notorious Communist guerrilla leader
Sam Boga and his band...</i>

538
01:03:23,081 --> 01:03:25,310
<i>...have crashed through into Botswana.</i>

539
01:03:25,449 --> 01:03:28,542
<i>- They are heading for Mozambique.
- Well, how many?</i>

540
01:03:28,718 --> 01:03:30,413
Not even 300.

541
01:03:30,587 --> 01:03:32,917
I told you bastards,
don't waste ammunition!

542
01:03:33,122 --> 01:03:35,419
Now we can't even fight back anymore.

543
01:03:35,590 --> 01:03:39,957
All of you switch your guns over
from automatic to single-fire.

544
01:03:40,394 --> 01:03:43,954
<i>Anyone withholding information
which could lead to their capture...</i>

545
01:03:44,130 --> 01:03:46,756
That's automatic. That's single.

546
01:03:46,965 --> 01:03:50,331
<i>Citizens are warned that Sam Boga
is a dangerous person...</i>

547
01:03:50,466 --> 01:03:55,027
<i>...and that he and his gang
are well-armed. So it'll be unwise...</i>

548
01:03:55,204 --> 01:03:56,965
And why are you so beautiful?

549
01:03:57,138 --> 01:03:59,402
I'm going to the school
to give her these.

550
01:03:59,573 --> 01:04:01,233
You gonna look like that?

551
01:04:01,409 --> 01:04:03,137
- Like what?
- Like it's a funeral.

552
01:04:03,343 --> 01:04:05,935
You've gotta smile
and tell her she looks good.

553
01:04:06,111 --> 01:04:07,941
How are you an expert on women?

554
01:04:08,112 --> 01:04:10,137
I got seven wives. How many you got?

555
01:04:10,348 --> 01:04:13,646
- Why aren't you at home with them?
- I know how to marry them.

556
01:04:13,850 --> 01:04:18,046
- Nobody knows how to live with them.
- So, what did you marry them for?

557
01:04:18,219 --> 01:04:22,847
Someday I have to tell you
the facts of life.

558
01:04:28,093 --> 01:04:31,926
"And yet we all agree
that every plate we break...

559
01:04:32,096 --> 01:04:34,724
...was cracked by Mr. Nobody.

560
01:04:34,898 --> 01:04:38,628
'Tis he who tears our books, who..."

561
01:04:56,579 --> 01:04:57,944
Come in.

562
01:04:58,448 --> 01:05:01,245
Good morning, Mr. Steyn.

563
01:05:02,616 --> 01:05:04,083
Morning, class.

564
01:05:04,686 --> 01:05:06,914
Good morning, Mr. Steyn.

565
01:05:07,621 --> 01:05:10,315
l...I brought...

566
01:05:35,540 --> 01:05:37,531
Please, just leave it.

567
01:05:39,677 --> 01:05:42,975
I brought you your shoes.

568
01:05:49,416 --> 01:05:50,906
Come in.

569
01:05:57,989 --> 01:05:59,615
Come in.

570
01:06:02,793 --> 01:06:05,158
Shoe.

571
01:06:24,741 --> 01:06:27,175
You don't want to talk about it, huh?

572
01:06:30,311 --> 01:06:32,210
Shame.

573
01:06:46,991 --> 01:06:49,823
<i>The animals looked ridiculous
but good to eat...</i>

574
01:06:49,993 --> 01:06:51,323
<i>...and he was hungry.</i>

575
01:07:24,383 --> 01:07:27,250
<i>Suddenly a young boy made
chattering noises at Xi.</i>

576
01:07:27,419 --> 01:07:30,215
<i>So he said, "I shot
one of those animals.</i>

577
01:07:30,387 --> 01:07:33,878
<i>It'll go to sleep soon,
and then we can eat it. "</i>

578
01:07:34,523 --> 01:07:39,391
<i>But the boy ran away, maybe to call
his family to join in the feast.</i>

579
01:08:00,641 --> 01:08:02,074
<i>There was a weird sound...</i>

580
01:08:02,243 --> 01:08:06,041
<i>...and another of those strange animals
with the round legs appeared.</i>

581
01:08:09,614 --> 01:08:13,243
<i>The young boy and a grownup got
out of it, and seemed very excited.</i>

582
01:08:13,450 --> 01:08:16,782
<i>Xi said, "Come, sit down.
There's enough meat for all of us. "</i>

583
01:08:21,556 --> 01:08:25,013
<i>But the man was rude and greedy.
He took the whole animal.</i>

584
01:08:28,094 --> 01:08:30,118
<i>He said, "You have very bad manners.</i>

585
01:08:30,295 --> 01:08:34,287
<i>If you eat the whole thing,
I'll have to shoot another for myself. "</i>

586
01:08:37,434 --> 01:08:40,163
<i>The man shouted,
but he didn't want anything to do...</i>

587
01:08:40,336 --> 01:08:43,566
<i>...with such an uncouth person,
so he ignored him.</i>

588
01:08:44,672 --> 01:08:46,571
<i>Suddenly there was a thunderclap.</i>

589
01:08:46,740 --> 01:08:50,402
<i>The animals ran away, and he ran
after them. He was very hungry.</i>

590
01:09:08,689 --> 01:09:10,246
Do you speak English?

591
01:09:10,423 --> 01:09:13,789
You are free to remain silent
until you have seen your lawyer.

592
01:09:13,959 --> 01:09:18,189
If you speak now, whatever you say will
be taken down as evidence against you.

593
01:09:35,141 --> 01:09:37,369
And why are you so beautiful?

594
01:09:37,576 --> 01:09:39,373
I got to go to court.

595
01:09:39,577 --> 01:09:41,101
What did you do?

596
01:09:41,278 --> 01:09:45,337
The cops were here. They say they
caught a little Bushman for stock theft.

597
01:09:45,981 --> 01:09:49,472
They say all he can speak is "Xixo,"
so they want me to interpret.

598
01:09:49,651 --> 01:09:49,817
Xixo.

599
01:09:49,817 --> 01:09:53,082
Xixo.

600
01:09:56,789 --> 01:09:59,848
<i>They brought Xi into a place
with several people.</i>

601
01:10:00,026 --> 01:10:03,892
<i>He smiled at them in greeting,
but nobody smiled back.</i>

602
01:10:14,502 --> 01:10:16,470
Interpreter.

603
01:10:23,841 --> 01:10:28,106
You, Xixo, are hereby charged with
wrongfully and unlawfully slaughtering...

604
01:10:28,245 --> 01:10:32,703
...one goat on the 21st of September,
1980, in Oniamatokwe.

605
01:10:32,914 --> 01:10:35,643
How plead you?
Guilty or not guilty?

606
01:10:36,483 --> 01:10:39,645
<i>Mpudi found it difficult to interpret
because, in his language...</i>

607
01:10:39,819 --> 01:10:41,843
<i>...there was no word for "guilty."</i>

608
01:10:44,556 --> 01:10:47,888
Finally he asked,
"Did you shoot an animal?"

609
01:10:48,058 --> 01:10:52,926
<i>Xi said, "Yes, I did, but that man took it.
He did not want to share it with me. "</i>

610
01:10:53,162 --> 01:10:56,562
- Well, what does he plead?
- Not guilty.

611
01:10:56,731 --> 01:11:01,167
- They gave him the death sentence.
- For killing a goat? No.

612
01:11:01,334 --> 01:11:06,269
Three months in jail, same thing.
He gonna die for sure.

613
01:11:06,504 --> 01:11:09,563
He never seen a wall.
Now, he got walls all around him.

614
01:11:09,740 --> 01:11:11,866
But didn't you explain to them?

615
01:11:12,042 --> 01:11:16,272
- They said, "Silence in court."
- Yeah, but surely they ought to know.

616
01:11:17,279 --> 01:11:19,906
Nobody knows the Bushmen.

617
01:11:20,680 --> 01:11:23,047
Nobody ever goes
into the deep Kalahari.

618
01:11:23,216 --> 01:11:25,843
How come you know so much
about them?

619
01:11:26,018 --> 01:11:30,716
When Botswana belonged to the British,
I hit a policeman for insulting my father.

620
01:11:30,888 --> 01:11:33,947
So I fled, right into the Kalahari.

621
01:11:34,157 --> 01:11:36,852
I died, you know. Dehydration.

622
01:11:37,026 --> 01:11:39,858
Some of those little buggers
found me, and buried me.

623
01:11:40,028 --> 01:11:41,358
Only my head stuck out.

624
01:11:41,528 --> 01:11:44,725
For two weeks, they pushed water
and food into my mouth.

625
01:11:44,898 --> 01:11:47,296
And when they dug me up,
I was nearly white.

626
01:11:47,466 --> 01:11:48,797
Like you.

627
01:11:49,102 --> 01:11:53,537
I lived with them for three years.
They're the sweetest little buggers.

628
01:11:53,704 --> 01:11:56,035
He gonna die for sure.

629
01:12:08,314 --> 01:12:11,112
Can I go to Mahadi tomorrow?

630
01:12:11,283 --> 01:12:13,750
You wanna go and see
little what's his name?

631
01:12:13,918 --> 01:12:16,112
I want to get him out.

632
01:12:16,286 --> 01:12:18,310
Now, don't do anything silly.

633
01:12:18,488 --> 01:12:20,581
They got to let him out.

634
01:12:21,690 --> 01:12:24,124
Maybe if we explain to them.

635
01:12:24,626 --> 01:12:27,889
- You coming too?
- Yes.

636
01:12:48,275 --> 01:12:51,402
Says he's sorry.
He try to eat the food tomorrow.

637
01:12:51,577 --> 01:12:55,479
- Has he eaten anything? It's been a week.
- No.

638
01:12:58,349 --> 01:13:00,908
Of course we're worried.
We can't force-feed him.

639
01:13:01,084 --> 01:13:03,916
- You've got to let him out.
- He's got 11 weeks to go.

640
01:13:04,086 --> 01:13:07,817
Well, is there no way?
Can't we buy him out or something?

641
01:13:07,990 --> 01:13:11,515
Well, if somebody wants to employ
him as a convict-labourer.

642
01:13:11,725 --> 01:13:14,250
But he has no experience,
no qualifications.

643
01:13:14,426 --> 01:13:16,155
He got qualifications.

644
01:13:16,328 --> 01:13:19,353
He can teach you things
about plants and animals.

645
01:13:19,532 --> 01:13:23,761
Yes. We want to employ him
as an ecological expert.

646
01:13:33,107 --> 01:13:35,870
He will have to remain in your employ
for the full 11 weeks.

647
01:13:36,042 --> 01:13:39,738
If he leaves, we will hunt him down
and lock him up for a long time.

648
01:13:39,878 --> 01:13:41,640
Okay, thanks.

649
01:13:57,157 --> 01:13:59,021
We can't put him inside.

650
01:13:59,192 --> 01:14:00,853
No, you're right.

651
01:14:45,357 --> 01:14:48,884
I understand the words,
but the meaning...

652
01:14:49,060 --> 01:14:53,358
Talks about a bad thing,
an evil thing.

653
01:14:53,529 --> 01:14:55,588
And about the end of the world.

654
01:14:55,798 --> 01:15:00,063
Well, explain to him he has
to stay with us for the full 11 weeks.

655
01:15:00,235 --> 01:15:04,431
- He doesn't know from weeks.
- We'll tell him when it's okay to go.

656
01:15:12,243 --> 01:15:14,733
- Hello, Andrew. Mpudi.
- Hello, Jack.

657
01:15:14,912 --> 01:15:17,004
I hear a Bushman's working for you.

658
01:15:17,180 --> 01:15:19,204
Yeah, his name is Xi.

659
01:15:19,381 --> 01:15:22,076
- Are they good trackers?
- Best in the world.

660
01:15:22,250 --> 01:15:23,615
Mind if I borrow him?

661
01:15:23,817 --> 01:15:26,547
One of my guests wounded a cougar.
My trackers can't find it.

662
01:15:33,391 --> 01:15:35,449
This is where we lost him.

663
01:15:56,407 --> 01:15:58,704
You'll see, he'll find him.

664
01:16:12,451 --> 01:16:14,748
Hey! Hey!

665
01:16:29,063 --> 01:16:30,997
Scram, go away!

666
01:16:32,265 --> 01:16:33,663
Get!

667
01:16:37,635 --> 01:16:39,125
Go away!

668
01:16:52,513 --> 01:16:56,744
- I'm sorry, I didn't realise...
- I don't want to talk about it.

669
01:17:07,824 --> 01:17:09,381
What do you want?

670
01:17:10,591 --> 01:17:13,457
Hurry up. Hurry up.
Get them out.

671
01:17:14,628 --> 01:17:16,892
Come on. Get him.
Hurry up, man.

672
01:17:29,772 --> 01:17:31,966
You can drop those guns.

673
01:17:39,913 --> 01:17:41,312
Bastard.

674
01:17:41,680 --> 01:17:43,409
You want me to let fly?

675
01:17:47,017 --> 01:17:50,110
Now get out.
With your hands up.

676
01:17:56,291 --> 01:17:58,121
Bring out all the kids.

677
01:18:01,494 --> 01:18:04,792
Sergeant, I'm going to walk due east
from here to Motambe...

678
01:18:04,997 --> 01:18:07,192
...and I'm taking
all these kids with me.

679
01:18:07,365 --> 01:18:10,527
If I see one truck or one aeroplane
or one policeman...

680
01:18:10,700 --> 01:18:13,190
...or one soldier or one person...

681
01:18:13,370 --> 01:18:15,929
...we'll mow these kids down.

682
01:18:16,070 --> 01:18:18,334
- Have you got shortwave in there?
- Yes.

683
01:18:18,840 --> 01:18:24,300
Now get on to headquarters, and tell them
I want a corridor 10 miles wide.

684
01:18:24,477 --> 01:18:28,138
The army and the police
better clear out everybody.

685
01:18:28,313 --> 01:18:31,679
And they've got to put down food
and water every 20 miles.

686
01:18:31,849 --> 01:18:36,011
And then get the hell out of the way
before we get there. Tell them that.

687
01:18:37,386 --> 01:18:41,321
All right, get them into a circle.
I want a big circle around me.

688
01:18:41,489 --> 01:18:44,946
Leave the small ones. It's miles
to Motambe. They'll never make it.

689
01:18:49,094 --> 01:18:50,526
Okay, now buzz off.

690
01:18:50,696 --> 01:18:52,685
Clear out the people from this end...

691
01:18:52,864 --> 01:18:55,991
...because I want to start marching
in two hours.

692
01:18:59,401 --> 01:19:02,666
And I warn you,
you better clear out everybody.

693
01:19:07,006 --> 01:19:08,473
Clutch.

694
01:19:13,912 --> 01:19:15,707
Brake. Brake.

695
01:19:16,747 --> 01:19:18,771
Clutch. Clutch!

696
01:19:23,017 --> 01:19:25,746
I'm teaching him to drive.
Just for the hell of it.

697
01:19:25,919 --> 01:19:28,386
Nothing else to do around here anyhow.

698
01:19:28,555 --> 01:19:31,580
- Still mooning about the schoolmarm?
- Sort of.

699
01:19:31,757 --> 01:19:35,123
I want to move up to Nioko for a
few days so we can do a game count.

700
01:19:35,293 --> 01:19:38,749
- How will this get us through the jungle?
- We strip it down.

701
01:19:54,306 --> 01:19:57,035
Come on, Xi. Come on!

702
01:20:01,745 --> 01:20:03,803
He don't know from doors.

703
01:20:39,838 --> 01:20:42,169
Stop playing that bloody game.

704
01:20:42,340 --> 01:20:44,637
Okay, it's time. Let's go.
Move them.

705
01:20:44,808 --> 01:20:46,173
Come on. Everybody up.

706
01:20:46,343 --> 01:20:49,310
Come on, let's go.
Keep them going.

707
01:20:49,478 --> 01:20:51,275
Keep them in a circle around me.

708
01:20:51,446 --> 01:20:53,936
Move them!
Don't leave any stragglers.

709
01:20:54,315 --> 01:20:56,475
- Keep your paws to yourself!
- Shut up.

710
01:20:57,917 --> 01:21:00,407
Get them into a circle.
A circle, a circle!

711
01:21:02,254 --> 01:21:05,188
- Stop yelling at them.
- That's not a bloody circle.

712
01:21:05,356 --> 01:21:07,915
- Can't you do anything right?
- I can't get them into a circle.

713
01:21:08,091 --> 01:21:09,819
They keep coming up in a square.

714
01:21:09,992 --> 01:21:12,688
Then, make it a square.
Let them walk in a square.

715
01:21:12,862 --> 01:21:15,796
Keep them going.
Don't let them straggle.

716
01:21:17,331 --> 01:21:19,162
Who says they'll come this way?

717
01:21:19,499 --> 01:21:22,797
He says he wants a corridor
10 miles wide.

718
01:21:23,068 --> 01:21:27,697
I'm sorry. We'll have to get out of the way
for now until he passes this point.

719
01:21:27,872 --> 01:21:29,805
Where can I find Andrew Steyn?

720
01:21:29,974 --> 01:21:32,806
You'd better warn him too.
He's five miles that way.

721
01:21:32,976 --> 01:21:34,442
You turn right at the...

722
01:21:34,610 --> 01:21:36,600
Damn it, I'll come and show you.

723
01:21:37,477 --> 01:21:39,969
Johnny, will you take them to Machadi?

724
01:21:56,158 --> 01:22:00,184
Tell them to sing.
Come on, everybody. Sing, sing!

725
01:23:24,353 --> 01:23:25,718
Wouldn't you know?

726
01:23:25,887 --> 01:23:27,445
Now where do we find him?

727
01:23:32,759 --> 01:23:34,658
They left this morning.

728
01:23:35,927 --> 01:23:37,394
Come on!

729
01:24:06,249 --> 01:24:07,715
They went through.

730
01:24:07,883 --> 01:24:09,816
They'll meet up with Boga for sure.

731
01:24:09,985 --> 01:24:13,613
- Is there a way around this?
- It's a hell of a long way.

732
01:24:13,787 --> 01:24:15,482
Well, let's go.

733
01:24:47,310 --> 01:24:48,800
Mpudi.

734
01:25:07,725 --> 01:25:13,252
One, two, three, four, five...

735
01:25:13,429 --> 01:25:15,521
...six adult oryx.

736
01:25:19,533 --> 01:25:22,365
He says there are people
things down there.

737
01:25:22,535 --> 01:25:24,594
- Where?
- Down there.

738
01:25:35,344 --> 01:25:37,811
Army truck. Unloading something.

739
01:25:39,881 --> 01:25:41,974
I wonder what they're up to.

740
01:25:45,284 --> 01:25:48,651
Looks like food.
Cooking pots and stuff.

741
01:25:49,287 --> 01:25:50,878
Maybe it's a picnic.

742
01:25:52,556 --> 01:25:54,387
Funny. They're going away.

743
01:25:56,859 --> 01:26:01,294
- They went away and left their stuff.
- Yeah, funny.

744
01:26:04,130 --> 01:26:05,154
Oh, well.

745
01:26:05,332 --> 01:26:07,857
One, two, three, four, five, six...

746
01:26:29,048 --> 01:26:31,015
You've got to let them rest.

747
01:26:31,183 --> 01:26:33,673
The smaller ones can't keep up.

748
01:26:33,852 --> 01:26:36,012
They can rest
when they get to the food.

749
01:26:36,186 --> 01:26:39,485
- You're driving them too hard.
- It's a long way to Motambe.

750
01:26:39,656 --> 01:26:42,818
You said 20 miles.
They can't walk 20 miles without eating.

751
01:26:42,991 --> 01:26:44,423
Halt!

752
01:26:52,198 --> 01:26:53,893
Look at that!

753
01:26:54,066 --> 01:26:57,933
I told you,
stop playing that bloody game!

754
01:27:02,438 --> 01:27:04,929
You've got to let
the little ones turn back.

755
01:27:05,107 --> 01:27:06,937
Nobody turns back.

756
01:27:07,108 --> 01:27:10,702
Next thing,
everybody's gonna get sore feet.

757
01:27:10,877 --> 01:27:13,709
Next one drops out, I shoot him!

758
01:27:14,079 --> 01:27:17,741
You, you, help her.
If you got to carry her, carry her.

759
01:27:18,249 --> 01:27:21,911
If I catch you playing again,
by God...

760
01:27:22,419 --> 01:27:23,943
March!

761
01:27:24,120 --> 01:27:27,112
They can't march 20 miles.
They're not soldiers!

762
01:27:27,322 --> 01:27:31,053
If they want to eat,
they'd better march 20 miles!

763
01:27:31,226 --> 01:27:36,594
Are you scared it'll spoil your image
if you admit you made a mistake?

764
01:27:37,929 --> 01:27:40,396
Halt!

765
01:27:47,103 --> 01:27:49,570
You! Come here!

766
01:27:55,142 --> 01:27:57,701
See that hill over there?

767
01:27:58,210 --> 01:28:01,975
Go to the top, and wave this thing
until the army people see you.

768
01:28:02,147 --> 01:28:08,278
Then you go down to them, and
tell them Sam Boga made a mistake.

769
01:28:11,953 --> 01:28:14,978
Now I want them to leave food
every 10 miles.

770
01:28:15,156 --> 01:28:16,884
- Understand?
- Yes.

771
01:28:17,056 --> 01:28:19,047
Now, get going. Move!

772
01:28:23,094 --> 01:28:25,153
March!

773
01:28:25,363 --> 01:28:27,592
One ostrich and four, five...

774
01:28:27,764 --> 01:28:30,357
...six, seven, eight...

775
01:28:41,074 --> 01:28:44,474
A lot of children. The food
must have been left there for them.

776
01:28:44,644 --> 01:28:47,076
- What the hell? They've got guns.
- The kids?

777
01:28:47,244 --> 01:28:51,509
No. There are men down there
with guns. It's no picnic.

778
01:28:51,981 --> 01:28:54,245
I think those kids are hostages.

779
01:28:54,417 --> 01:28:57,111
What was that on the news
about Sam Boga?

780
01:29:02,255 --> 01:29:06,451
That man said I must go to the top,
and I must wave my conga.

781
01:29:12,796 --> 01:29:14,786
So Miss Kate said 20 miles
is too much.

782
01:29:14,964 --> 01:29:17,296
- Is she down there?
- Yes.

783
01:29:28,674 --> 01:29:30,937
We'll have to immobilise them.

784
01:29:31,542 --> 01:29:34,408
- Are Bushmen good stalkers?
- Best in the world.

785
01:29:34,544 --> 01:29:36,478
Let him have a look at them.

786
01:29:43,685 --> 01:29:45,049
All right.

787
01:29:45,219 --> 01:29:50,120
Explain to him that the men with the guns
are bad. We have to put them to sleep.

788
01:29:56,359 --> 01:29:59,123
He want to know how did
those people get in there?

789
01:29:59,295 --> 01:30:01,956
No, no, they're not...

790
01:30:02,998 --> 01:30:04,487
You explain.

791
01:30:04,665 --> 01:30:06,656
One hour, then we move!

792
01:30:06,834 --> 01:30:09,062
I'm gonna have a snooze.

793
01:30:33,952 --> 01:30:35,249
"Dear Miss Thompson:

794
01:30:35,454 --> 01:30:39,980
Your abductors have been injected
with an immobiliser.

795
01:30:40,491 --> 01:30:43,720
When they go to sleep,
you must disarm them."

796
01:30:44,593 --> 01:30:48,255
Tell him he must give her the note
only after he's shot all the men.

797
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:55,827
When he shoots, he must
pull back on the thread quickly...

798
01:30:56,002 --> 01:30:59,994
...so the man can think it was a horsefly
or a wasp that stung him.

799
01:31:09,777 --> 01:31:11,608
He's fast. It'll work.

800
01:31:11,778 --> 01:31:14,474
He must dip the needle each time.

801
01:31:49,538 --> 01:31:52,005
I can't see the little bugger.

802
01:31:52,273 --> 01:31:54,070
Yeah, I see him.

803
01:32:13,522 --> 01:32:14,954
Now, look at that.

804
01:32:15,590 --> 01:32:17,615
Yeah, he's clever.

805
01:33:23,504 --> 01:33:25,368
Nothing's happening down there.

806
01:33:25,572 --> 01:33:27,369
It takes time.

807
01:33:33,479 --> 01:33:35,309
Who are you?

808
01:34:18,610 --> 01:34:22,374
Some of those guys are down.
She'll need help when they wake up.

809
01:34:24,413 --> 01:34:27,974
Hey, wake up, man.
You gotta wake up.

810
01:34:28,150 --> 01:34:31,915
Come on, you can't sleep now.
Come on.

811
01:34:55,936 --> 01:34:58,732
We need some rope.
There's plenty in the Land Rover.

812
01:34:58,904 --> 01:35:01,634
He can fetch it.
I didn't teach him for nothing.

813
01:35:06,776 --> 01:35:09,005
Says he don't understand the gears.

814
01:35:10,778 --> 01:35:13,679
- Told him he can drive in any gear.
- Let's go!

815
01:35:13,848 --> 01:35:15,543
And you take that one.

816
01:35:15,716 --> 01:35:17,945
And you, that one.

817
01:35:18,151 --> 01:35:19,174
And I'll take...

818
01:35:20,886 --> 01:35:23,353
There's only six.
There should be eight.

819
01:35:32,461 --> 01:35:35,726
Maybe they're asleep as well.
I don't know.

820
01:35:39,567 --> 01:35:40,964
All right.

821
01:35:41,400 --> 01:35:44,528
I want you to circulate
among the children.

822
01:35:44,702 --> 01:35:48,228
Quietly. And tell them that
when we grab the guns...

823
01:35:48,406 --> 01:35:52,067
...they must run fast into that crevice
behind us and take cover.

824
01:35:52,241 --> 01:35:54,402
Okay? Good.

825
01:36:06,451 --> 01:36:09,284
Ready? Go!

826
01:36:15,557 --> 01:36:17,047
Come on!

827
01:36:25,064 --> 01:36:27,259
No! Get down, get down!

828
01:36:28,233 --> 01:36:29,996
And stay there!

829
01:36:34,437 --> 01:36:36,428
Get back! All of you!

830
01:36:38,507 --> 01:36:40,236
- Hey, watch it!
- Sorry.

831
01:36:52,083 --> 01:36:56,416
We've got to outflank them.
You go around. I'll keep you covered.

832
01:37:18,168 --> 01:37:20,159
Get back! Get back!

833
01:37:21,037 --> 01:37:22,799
Hurry up!

834
01:37:35,047 --> 01:37:36,536
- You okay?
- Yep.

835
01:37:36,748 --> 01:37:38,510
- Who are they shooting at?
- I don't know.

836
01:37:43,285 --> 01:37:45,515
Four, five, six.

837
01:37:45,687 --> 01:37:47,051
Two are missing.

838
01:37:47,255 --> 01:37:49,950
This one here, and I heard
shots from over there.

839
01:37:59,530 --> 01:38:00,554
Look.

840
01:38:16,809 --> 01:38:18,469
Roll over.

841
01:38:20,278 --> 01:38:22,006
Mpudi, hold him.

842
01:39:48,640 --> 01:39:50,540
What's happened?

843
01:39:50,974 --> 01:39:52,941
Have you got water in there?

844
01:39:53,377 --> 01:39:55,105
Hold these for me.

845
01:39:59,848 --> 01:40:02,644
- Get up.
- But what happened, man?

846
01:40:02,850 --> 01:40:04,749
Oh, it's a long story.

847
01:40:05,251 --> 01:40:08,083
What happened to those guys?
Are they all dead?

848
01:40:09,754 --> 01:40:11,120
Did you kill them?

849
01:40:11,289 --> 01:40:12,916
They've been immobilised.

850
01:40:13,457 --> 01:40:15,356
Where's Kate and the kids?

851
01:40:15,492 --> 01:40:18,255
They're hiding back there.
They can come out now.

852
01:40:18,427 --> 01:40:20,088
Oh, my God. Mpudi.

853
01:40:21,863 --> 01:40:23,922
Keep that guy covered.

854
01:40:30,969 --> 01:40:35,268
Kate! It's okay.
You can come out now!

855
01:40:38,740 --> 01:40:41,573
We've got everything under control.
You can come out!

856
01:40:41,743 --> 01:40:44,734
- Jack?
- Hi there. The marines have landed.

857
01:40:44,912 --> 01:40:47,244
It's okay. You can all come out.

858
01:40:48,181 --> 01:40:50,741
All right, come on. Come on.

859
01:41:07,162 --> 01:41:08,185
You're safe now.

860
01:41:08,395 --> 01:41:12,330
Better collect those men before
they wake up. You were right.

861
01:41:12,497 --> 01:41:15,489
- Did you fix him good?
- Yeah, get up.

862
01:41:17,268 --> 01:41:18,895
Walk.

863
01:41:28,276 --> 01:41:30,800
Boy, you had a tough time, huh?

864
01:41:31,545 --> 01:41:32,603
Watch out!

865
01:41:32,778 --> 01:41:34,405
Stop fooling around, Steyn.

866
01:41:35,548 --> 01:41:37,606
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

867
01:41:54,661 --> 01:41:56,150
I'm sorry.

868
01:41:56,329 --> 01:41:58,796
It's all right, Steyn. Move.

869
01:42:07,436 --> 01:42:09,300
Milady.

870
01:42:11,139 --> 01:42:15,131
Sergeant, get on the radio and organise
some buses to take the kids home.

871
01:42:15,675 --> 01:42:17,871
How come suddenly he the big hero?

872
01:42:19,012 --> 01:42:21,808
We'd better get back to our equipment.

873
01:42:32,687 --> 01:42:35,952
Says thank you, goodbye and
hopes you have lots of children.

874
01:42:36,089 --> 01:42:38,853
- Tell him thanks. I'll miss him.
- He can't use that.

875
01:42:39,026 --> 01:42:41,357
- I have to...
- Bushmen don't know about money.

876
01:42:41,660 --> 01:42:44,651
- What can I give him?
- There's nothing here he can use.

877
01:42:44,828 --> 01:42:48,662
- Bushmen don't need things.
- He's gotta take the money. It's the law.

878
01:42:55,771 --> 01:42:58,738
He's going the wrong way.
The Kalahari's that way.

879
01:43:02,207 --> 01:43:05,040
Says he got to find the
evil thing and get rid of it.

880
01:43:05,344 --> 01:43:07,004
I don't know.

881
01:43:07,879 --> 01:43:11,507
- I'm going to miss the little bugger.
- Yeah, me too.

882
01:43:11,681 --> 01:43:14,171
- You gonna look like that forever?
- Like what?

883
01:43:14,350 --> 01:43:16,340
Like Jack Hind is better than you.

884
01:43:16,519 --> 01:43:19,919
- No, I'm going to talk to her.
- Tell her you were the big hero.

885
01:43:20,087 --> 01:43:21,714
No, I can't do that.

886
01:43:21,922 --> 01:43:24,082
But I do want to talk to her.

887
01:43:24,290 --> 01:43:25,847
I'll tell her...

888
01:43:26,258 --> 01:43:29,124
I'll say, "Look, Miss Thompson...

889
01:43:29,560 --> 01:43:31,494
...I know you think I'm an idiot...

890
01:43:31,629 --> 01:43:33,892
...but normally I'm quite normal.

891
01:43:34,064 --> 01:43:37,056
It's only when I'm in the presence
of a lady that I...

892
01:43:37,232 --> 01:43:40,723
It's really just an interesting
psychological phenomenon.

893
01:43:40,902 --> 01:43:45,564
If a man who is susceptible to a type
of para-Freudian syndrome like this...

894
01:43:45,772 --> 01:43:48,239
...encounters a nubile
female, what happens?"

895
01:43:48,874 --> 01:43:51,273
I suppose another big word happens.

896
01:43:51,876 --> 01:43:54,867
- Too erudite?
- Yeah, whatever that means.

897
01:43:55,112 --> 01:43:57,875
Okay. I'll put it more simply. I'll say:

898
01:43:58,748 --> 01:44:00,544
"Look, Miss Thompson.

899
01:44:01,283 --> 01:44:04,080
Kate. Kate.

900
01:44:04,318 --> 01:44:07,616
It's really only an interesting
psychological phenomenon."

901
01:44:07,787 --> 01:44:10,584
She'll understand that bit.
She's a schoolteacher.

902
01:44:10,789 --> 01:44:13,655
I'll say, "When there's no lady present...

903
01:44:13,825 --> 01:44:16,259
...I can catch an insect
without hurting it."

904
01:44:16,427 --> 01:44:19,417
If she knew me better, she'd
see I'm not a stumblebum.

905
01:44:19,595 --> 01:44:24,122
- All I need is a little practise. If I...
- Wait for me. You need moral support.

906
01:44:45,147 --> 01:44:46,614
There she is.

907
01:44:50,851 --> 01:44:53,842
You better do your thing
before the pupils come.

908
01:44:54,153 --> 01:44:55,677
Yeah.

909
01:45:02,059 --> 01:45:03,548
Morning.

910
01:45:04,359 --> 01:45:06,122
Morning, Miss Thompson.

911
01:45:06,495 --> 01:45:08,121
Morning.

912
01:45:08,363 --> 01:45:10,592
- How are you?
- Fine, thanks. How are you?

913
01:45:10,764 --> 01:45:12,458
